OL,5, An advertising campaign for Tesco      
OL,6, Mobile which used the names of foods as
OL,7, substitutes for expletives has been    
OL,8, banned.                                
OL,10,FThe newspaper ads, Twitter posts and   
OL,11,Foutdoor posters used words like        
OL,12,F"shiitake" and "pistachio" instead of  
OL,13,Fswear words.                           
OL,15,FThe Advertising Standards Authority    
OL,16,Fsaid they were likely to cause "serious
OL,17,Fand widespread offence".               
OL,19,FTesco apologised and said it was trying
OL,20,Fto portray customer frustration.       
